Best husband appreciation post incoming…
.
A few weeks ago we received a YouTube comment that read something like “Chris, what do you even do?” While I know the comment was light-hearted in nature, a better question would have been what doesn’t he do? 
.
This amazing hard-working man does all the grocery shopping & cooking for our family, cleans the house, takes care of our finances, spends time daily with our boys playing teaching & loving on them, records, edits and uploads every single YouTube video, created a free reseller spreadsheet (link in our link tree if you need one 😝) to help others which has been downloaded over 12,000 times! He helps me whenever I ask, & he fixes all the things. 
.
For the last couple of weeks he’s been on his hands & knees several hours a day trying to get our flooring installed as quickly as possible (without sacrificing quality) so we can get back to our normal work flow/YouTube routine. Thank you all for your patience & support as we knock out this much needed project. We are planning our normal Thursday night live tomorrow (2/23) at 8pm MST if anyone wants to hang out & chat! 
.
.
.

Feeling extremely proud/emotional/grateful/hopeful today. Little Cathy couldn’t have even dreamed up the life I’m currently living. Little Cathy didn’t know finding a loving supportive hardworking husband, having children, owning a home, owning her own business were even slight possibilities for her life. 
Part of Chris & I’s retirement plan has been to own a few houses & rent them out. Today that plan got a little more real as we closed on our second home! Our current home will become a rental soon. Little Cathy didn’t have much hope for her future. Adult Cathy is confident the best is yet to come.
